    "gp_section_607021007093367351": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "d3564a57f7a5192aff42c9d945ed33bef99ab362058905cbc5a6efb032fd4a17_1_1_0_0__1",
        "ggCpMlV4Kwa_text": "There's a Way to Support Stuctural Space: Gradual Expansion Support",
        "ggDcqEtwral_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/851930ca66ce31a899a699ab530bd93596946988.jpg",
        "ggUWx6FTrjk_text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Your teeth have a natural curve called the Curve of Spee. This curve isn't random—it's engineered.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">The curve reflects the health of the skull in our view. Orthodontics will often flatten this curve either intentionally or unintentionally</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">This isn't theoretical. We have hundreds of people in our community that did braces and got:</span></p>",
        "ggW6c5vCIMc_text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Reviv doesn't straighten teeth the way braces do. It supports natural facial balance and encourages structural integrity.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Reviv works on a different principle than orthodontics.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Rather than traditional methods, Reviv focuses on providing vertical support to your bite:</span></p>",
        "ggX6Gl7rClt_text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">If you got braces and then noticed:</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- You felt a shift in your daily energy or mental clarity</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- You noticed gradual changes in your overall well-being over the years</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- You felt your facial aesthetics were changing prematurely</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Your physical drive or performance didn't feel the same</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- You noticed a shift in your general mood and ease</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">... you weren't imagining it. There is a connection.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Most traditional approaches focus primarily on the teeth, often overlooking the broader impact on jaw positioning.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">But thousands of people are now connecting the dots, and the pattern is undeniable.</span></p>",
        "ggX8JEL8fCf_text": "You Got Braces To Fix Your Teeth. But Some Treatments May Have Unintended Structural Effects. Dentist Probably Damaged Your Skull.",
        "ggdhahSmBqf_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/bae9e017d8ce3c1a4a3dee522680c31d7b1f9464.png",
        "ggj9eXNZ_zV_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/adb94291ef899f874f876c38f04e3f103efc0d27-Picsart-AiImageEnhancer.png",
        "ggjVFZ-f1q2_text": "How Certain Dental Changes May Affect Structural Space Over Time: The Curve of Spee",
        "ggor7kGraL-_text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\"><strong>Here's what happened:</strong></span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Your orthodontist straightened your teeth. But to do that, they had to change your bite in a way that most likely damaged your skull.&nbsp;</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">What you didn't know: Your skull operates like a balloon with 29 interconnected bones. When your orthodontist compressed your dental structure, they likely deflated that balloon.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">And when the balloon deflates, everything inside collapses.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">And that's when the real problems start</span></p>",
        "ggqxfir1zgx_text": "You're Not Crazy. Your Health Didn't<br>Randomly Decline.",
        "ggrwGxsfgrx_text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Supports your jaw in finding its natural, optimal position.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Encourages space and positioning that may have &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;changed over time..</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Supports more natural breathing patterns.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Supports overall well-being and mental clarity</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
        "ggw5SyJIsl0_text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Jaw tension or facial tightness</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Changes some people associate with reduced clarity</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Disrupted sleep patterns</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Shifts in posture and overall alignment</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Changes in facial aesthetics over time</span></p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-607021007093367351"
    },
